Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo has shared a photograph of himself at the Duchess International Hospital, following his recent surgery. On July 16, a surgical procedure was carried out on the vice-president, following “recurrent pain” in his leg. In a message posted on his social media handles on Sunday, Osinbajo thanked the medical personnel for their efforts. He also expressed his appreciation to Nigerians for their messages and prayers over his health. “My deep gratitude to everyone for your get-well wishes and prayers following my surgery,” he wrote. “And special appreciation to the amazing team of surgeons, doctors, nurses, physiotherapists, and the management of the Duchess International Hospital Lagos @duchesshospital , for providing such excellent care. “God bless you all.” See photo below. From third left: Tokunbo Shitta-Bey, CEO, Duchess Hospital; Dolapo, Osinbajo’s wife; Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo; and Nic Audifferen, Osinbajo’s chief personal physician. Photo: Tolani Alli 